1. Project Overview

This is a full-stack Blog application with both frontend and backend.

Frontend: React, Tailwind CSS

Backend: Node.js, Express

Database: MongoDB

Features: Create, read, delete (CRUD) blogs, user authentication, image upload, and role-based access.


2. Setup & Installation

Backend

1. Navigate to backend folder:
cd server

2. Install dependencies:
npm install

3. Create .env file with following variables:
PORT=8080
MONGO_URI=<your-mongodb-uri>
ACCESS_JWT_SECRET=<jwt-access-secret>
REFRESH_JWT_SECRET=<jwt-refresh-secret>
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=<cloud-name>
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=<api-key>
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=<api-secret>

4. Start the backend server:
npm run dev


Frontend

1. Navigate to frontend folder:
cd client

2. Install dependencies:
npm install

3. Create .env file with following variable:
VITE_BACKEND_URI=http://localhost:8080

4. Start the frontend server:
npm run dev